# DevOps Internship - Task 1: CI/CD Pipeline using GitHub Actions

As part of my DevOps Internship at Elevate Labs, I completed a hands-on task to automate the build and deployment workflow of a Node.js application using GitHub Actions and Docker.

### What I implemented

* Created a CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions.
* Automated dependency installation and test execution.
* Built a Docker image for the Node.js application.
* Pushed the Docker image to Docker Hub automatically on code changes.
* Configured workflow triggers on GitHub repository events.

### Technologies Used

* GitHub
* GitHub Actions
* Node.js
* Docker
* Docker Hub

### Key Learnings

* Understanding the CI/CD lifecycle and automation process.
* Writing and configuring GitHub Actions workflow YAML files.
* Working with GitHub Actions runners, jobs, and steps.
* Managing secrets securely in GitHub Actions.
* Building and publishing Docker images.
* Troubleshooting CI/CD pipeline issues and deployment workflows.

### Outcome

This task provided practical experience in implementing CI/CD pipelines and helped me understand how modern DevOps teams automate software delivery processes.
